            <h2>Welcome to Science 10</h2>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p><b>Alberta Science 10 Outcomes</b></p>
<p>The Science 10 curriculum provides a foundation for scientific literacy by developing knowledge, skills, and attitudes necessary for understanding scientific principles and their applications. Students will:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Understand and apply fundamental scientific concepts across multiple disciplines</li>
    <li>Develop inquiry and problem-solving skills through scientific investigation</li>
    <li>Analyze and interpret experimental data to make informed conclusions</li>
    <li>Recognize the interconnections between science, technology, and the environment</li>
    <li>Communicate scientific ideas effectively using appropriate terminology and methods</li>
    <li>Demonstrate safe and responsible practices in scientific experiments</li>
</ul>
<p>By achieving these outcomes, students will:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Apply scientific principles to real-world problems and societal issues</li>
    <li>Engage in critical thinking and evidence-based decision-making</li>
    <li>Develop an appreciation for the impact of scientific advancements</li>
    <li>Understand energy flow, chemical processes, and the dynamic nature of Earthâ€™s systems</li>
    <li>Demonstrate curiosity and a commitment to lifelong scientific learning</li>
</ul>



